title: Sample Book (France & United States), 1920–30
inscribed: Stamped on inside of front cover: H.A. Elsberg 51 East 57th St. New York
creditline: Gift of the Estate of Herman A. Elsberg
description: Sample book with paper leaves bound in grey cloth covers. Pages number 1-249; on sixty-nine pages are samples of silk ribbons. On three pages are watercolor design for ribbons.

tombstone.epitaph: Sample Book (France & United States), 1920–30; Designed by Herman A. Elsberg (American, 1869–1938); silk, metallic thread; H x W: 40.8 × 29 cm (16 1/16 × 11 7/16 in.); Gift of the Estate of Herman A. Elsberg; 1941-60-1
